com.siperian.sif.message.hm

Class EntityFilterCriteria

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.hm.EntityFilterCriteria
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class EntityFilterCriteria
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This is the filter criteria for GetOneHopRequest and also EntityGraphFilter. Each criterion describes the entity type and the specific data values described in the filterParameters of the entity records to be returned. Data values of related child records can be specified. For example, when retrieving People entity records, the data criteria can specify STATE = CA where STATE is a field of the child Address table.
    See Also:
    GetOneHopRequest, EntityGraphFilter, Serialized Form

      • setFilterCriteria

        public void setFilterCriteria(String filterCriteria)
        Specifies the filter conditions for the query. May be used to specify the literal expressions (FIRST_NAME = 'JOHN') or it may be used in combination with the setFilterParameters(ArrayList) to specify the parameterized queries (FIRST_NAME = ?) when the specific values for the parameter are provided as a list through the setFilterParameters(ArrayList) method.

        Parameters:
        filterCriteria - SQL condition clause used to select records.

      • getFilterParameters

        public ArrayList getFilterParameters()
        Returns:
        ArrayList of Parameter objects; Never returns null.

      • setFilterParameters

        public void setFilterParameters(ArrayList filterParameters)
        Used to set parameters in the filter criteria specified in setFilterCriteria(String).

        Each element in the list is matched to the place holders specified in the filter criteria by ? symbols. The list is expected to hold Parameter objects.

        Parameters:
        filterParameters - ArrayList of Parameter objects.
